<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Greycode Docs</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6; /* Improved line height for readability */
        }

        .sidebar {
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            height: 100vh;
            width: 280px; /* Wider sidebar */
            overflow-y: auto;
            background-color: #f9fafb; /* Softer background */
            padding: 2rem;
            border-right: 1px solid #e5e7eb; /* Subtle border */
        }

        .main-content {
            margin-left: 300px; /* Adjusted margin */
            padding: 2rem;
            flex: 1;
        }

        .sidebar a {
            display: block;
            padding: 0.75rem 0; /* Increased padding */
            color: #374151;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 500; /* Slightly bolder links */
            transition: color 0.3s;
        }

        .sidebar a:hover {
            color: #4f46e5;
        }

        code {
            font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, "Liberation Mono", "Courier New", monospace;
            background-color: #f3f4f6;
            padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
            border-radius: 0.25rem;
        }

        pre {
            background-color: #f3f4f6;
            padding: 1rem;
            border-radius: 0.5rem;
            overflow-x: auto;
            font-size: 0.875rem; /* Slightly smaller code font */
        }
        h1, h2, h3{
            font-weight: 700;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-white">
    <div class="flex">
        <aside class="sidebar">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-6 text-gray-800">Table of Contents</h2>
            <nav>
              <a href="#welcome">🚀 Welcome</a>
              <a href="#getting-started">🛠️ Getting Started</a>
              <a href="#structure">🗂️ Framework Structure</a>
              <a href="#how-it-works">⚙️ How It Works</a>
              <a href="#github">🔗 GitHub</a>
              <a href="#developers">🧑‍💻 Developers & Contributors</a>
            </nav>
        </aside>

        <main class="main-content">
            <section id="welcome" class="mb-12">
                <h1 class="text-4xl text-indigo-700 mb-4 ">Welcome to Greycodejs! 🎉</h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">The best Express.js framework to get started easily with web development using Express. ⚡</p>
            </section>

            <section id="getting-started" class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-2xl text-gray-800 mb-4">🛠️ Getting Started</h2>
                <pre>
                    <code class="text-gray-800">
                        // Install dependencies<br>
                        npm install<br><br>
                        // Create model<br>
                        gray.js create-model model_name<br><br>
                        // Migrate database<br>
                        gray.js migrate
                    </code>
                </pre>
            </section>

            <section id="structure" class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-2xl text-gray-800 mb-4">🗂️ Framework Structure</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The GreyCode.js framework is designed to streamline the development of applications using Sequelize and Express.js.</p>
                <pre>
                  <code class="text-gray-800">
                    Folder Structure Overview:<br>
                    ├── bin/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Command-line entry points for the application</span><br>
                    ├── config/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Configuration files (e.g., database settings)</span><br>
                    ├── controllers/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Controller files for handling business logic</span><br>
                    ├── core/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Core framework utilities and functionalities</span><br>
                    ├── middlewares/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Middleware functions for request/response handling</span><br>
                    ├── models/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Sequelize models for database interaction</span><br>
                    ├── node_modules/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Node.js dependencies</span><br>
                    ├── public/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Public assets (e.g., static files like images, CSS, JS)</span><br>
                    ├── routes/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Route definitions for mapping URLs to controllers</span><br>
                    ├── seeds/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Seed files for populating the database with initial data</span><br>
                    ├── templates/ <span class="text-gray-500"># Templates for generating code or HTML</span><br>
                    ├── .env <span class="text-gray-500"># Environment variable configuration</span><br>
                    ├── app.js <span class="text-gray-500"># Main application entry point</span><br>
                    ├── package.json <span class="text-gray-500"># Node.js package configuration</span><br>
                    └── README.md <span class="text-gray-500"># Documentation for the project</span>
                </code>
                </pre>
            </section>

            <section id="how-it-works" class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-2xl text-gray-800 mb-4">⚙️ How It Works</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-700">The framework is designed to be flexible. You can generate models, controllers, and routes via CLI commands like <code>gray.js create-model</code>, and manage them within the appropriate directories.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="github" class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-2xl text-gray-800 mb-4">🔗 GitHub</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-700">For more detailed documentation, please refer to the full documentation on GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/kculz/greycodejs/blob/main/README.md" target="_blank" class="text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-800">GreyCode.js Full Documentation</a></p>
            </section>

            <section id="developers" class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-2xl text-gray-800 mb-4">🧑‍💻 Developers & Contributors</h2>
                <ul class="mt-1">
                    <% devs.forEach(function(dev) { %>
                    <li><%= dev.name %> - <%= dev.role %></li>
                    <% }) %>
                </ul>
            </section>
        </main>
    </div>
</body>
</html>